#. Tag: title
#: net_dns.xml:9
#, no-c-format
msgid "The Domain Name System"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: net_dns.xml:12
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"DNS (domain name system) is needed to resolve the domain names and host "
"names into IP addresses. In this way, the IP address &wsIip; is assigned to "
"the host name <literal>&wsI;</literal> , for example. Before setting up your "
"own name server, read the general information about DNS in <xref linkend="
"\"sec.network.nameres\"/> . The following configuration examples refer to "
"BIND, the default DNS server."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: dm:translation
#: net_dns.xml:23
#, no-c-format
msgid "yes"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: net_dns.xml:28
#, no-c-format
msgid "DNS Terminology"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: net_dns.xml:32
#, no-c-format
msgid "Zone"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: net_dns.xml:34
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The domain name space is divided into regions called zones. For example, if "
"you have <literal>&exampledomain;</literal> , you have the <literal>example</"
"literal> section (or zone) of the <literal>com</literal> domain."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: net_dns.xml:43
#, no-c-format
msgid "DNS server"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: net_dns.xml:45
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The DNS server is a server that maintains the name and IP information for a "
"domain. You can have a primary DNS server for master zone, a secondary "
"server for slave zone, or a slave server without any zones for caching."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: net_dns.xml:52
#, no-c-format
msgid "Master zone DNS server"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: net_dns.xml:54
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The master zone includes all hosts from your network and a DNS server master "
"zone stores up-to-date records for all the hosts in your domain."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: net_dns.xml:62
#, no-c-format
msgid "Slave zone DNS server"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: net_dns.xml:64
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"A slave zone is a copy of the master zone. The slave zone DNS server obtains "
"its zone data with zone transfer operations from its master server. The "
"slave zone DNS server responds authoritatively for the zone as long as it "
"has valid (not expired) zone data. If the slave cannot obtain a new copy of "
"the zone data, it stops responding for the zone."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: net_dns.xml:78
#, no-c-format
msgid "Forwarder"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: net_dns.xml:80
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Forwarders are DNS servers to which your DNS server should send queries it "
"cannot answer. To enable different configuration sources in one "
"configuration, <literal>netconfig</literal> is used (see also <command>man 8 "
"netconfig</command> )."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: net_dns.xml:89
#, no-c-format
msgid "Record"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: net_dns.xml:91
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The record is information about name and IP address. Supported records and "
"their syntax are described in BIND documentation. Some special records are:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: net_dns.xml:98
#, no-c-format
msgid "NS record"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: net_dns.xml:100
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"An NS record tells name servers which machines are in charge of a given "
"domain zone."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: net_dns.xml:107
#, no-c-format
msgid "MX record"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: net_dns.xml:109
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The MX (mail exchange) records describe the machines to contact for "
"directing mail across the Internet."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: net_dns.xml:116
#, no-c-format
msgid "SOA record"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: net_dns.xml:118
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"SOA (Start of Authority) record is the first record in a zone file. The SOA "
"record is used when using DNS to synchronize data between multiple computers."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: net_dns.xml:132
#, no-c-format
msgid "Installation"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: net_dns.xml:134
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"To install a DNS server, start &yast; and select "
"<menuchoice><guimenu>Software</guimenu> <guimenu>Software Management</"
"guimenu></menuchoice> . Choose <menuchoice><guimenu>View</guimenu> "
"<guimenu>Patterns</guimenu></menuchoice> and select <guimenu>DHCP and DNS "
"Server</guimenu> . Confirm the installation of the dependent packages to "
"finish the installation process."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: net_dns.xml:142
#, no-c-format
msgid "Alternatively use the following command on the command line:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: net_dns.xml:145
#, no-c-format
msgid "&prompt.sudo;zypper in -t pattern dhcp_dns_server"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: net_dns.xml:149
#, no-c-format
msgid "Configuration with &yast;"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: net_dns.xml:151
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Use the &yast; DNS module to configure a DNS server for the local network. "
"When starting the module for the first time, a wizard starts, prompting you "
"to make a few decisions concerning administration of the server. Completing "
"this initial setup produces a basic server configuration. Use the expert "
"mode to deal with more advanced configuration tasks, such as setting up "
"ACLs, logging, TSIG keys, and other options."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: net_dns.xml:161
#, no-c-format
msgid "Wizard Configuration"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: net_dns.xml:164
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The wizard consists of three steps or dialogs. At the appropriate places in "
"the dialogs, you can enter the expert configuration mode."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: net_dns.xml:170
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<!-- 2014-04-24, ke: bnc#875014: asking for clarification --> <!-- ATM, it "
"is rather generic --> <!-- 2014-05-13, ke: Thus far (beta6), it is still "
"somehow open... --> When starting the module for the first time, the "
"<guimenu>Forwarder Settings</guimenu> dialog, shown in <xref linkend=\"fig."
"yast2.dnsinst.forwarders\"/> , opens. The <guimenu>Local DNS Resolution "
"Policy</guimenu> allows to set the following options:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: net_dns.xml:181
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<guimenu>Merging forwarders is disabled</guimenu> <!-- (= disable DNS "
"configuration updates via netconfig by setting NETCONFIG_DNS_POLICY='') -->"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: net_dns.xml:188
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<guimenu>Automatic merging</guimenu> <!-- (= enable automatic DNS "
"configuration updates via netconfig by setting NETCONFIG_DNS_POLICY='auto'; "
"behavior depends on nw in use or not; netconfig will update resolv.conf with "
"info (forwarder list) provided by dhcp/ppp) -->"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: net_dns.xml:201
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<guimenu>Merging forwarders is enabled</guimenu> <!-- "
"(NETCONFIG_DNS_POLICY='static') -->"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: net_dns.xml:207
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<!-- (NETCONFIG_DNS_POLICY='STATIC').--> <guimenu>Custom configuration</"
"guimenu> &mdash;If <guimenu>Custom configuration</guimenu> is selected, "
"<guimenu>Custom policy</guimenu> can be specified; by default (with "
"<guimenu>Automatic merging</guimenu> selected), <guimenu>Custom policy</"
"guimenu> is set to <literal>auto</literal> , but here you can either set "
"interface names or select from the two special policy names <literal>STATIC</"
"literal> and <literal>STATIC_FALLBACK</literal> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: net_dns.xml:225
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"In <guimenu>Local DNS Resolution Forwarder</guimenu> , specify which service "
"to use: <guimenu>Using system name servers</guimenu> , <guimenu>This name "
"server (bind)</guimenu> , or <guimenu>Local dnsmasq server</guimenu> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: net_dns.xml:231
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"For more information about all these settings, see <command>man 8 netconfig</"
"command> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: net_dns.xml:236
#, no-c-format
msgid "DNS Server Installation: Forwarder Settings"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: net_dns.xml:246
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Forwarders are DNS servers to which your DNS server sends queries it cannot "
"answer itself. Enter their IP address and click <guimenu>Add</guimenu> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: net_dns.xml:253
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The <guimenu>DNS Zones</guimenu> dialog consists of several parts and is "
"responsible for the management of zone files, described in <xref linkend="
"\"sec.dns.zonefile\"/> . For a new zone, provide a name for it in "
"<guimenu>Name</guimenu> . To add a reverse zone, the name must end in "
"<literal>.in-addr.arpa</literal> . Finally, select the <guimenu>Type</"
"guimenu> (master, slave, or forward). See <xref linkend=\"fig.yast2.dnsinst."
"zones\"/> . Click <guimenu>Edit </guimenu> to configure other settings of an "
"existing zone. To remove a zone, click <guimenu>Delete</guimenu> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: net_dns.xml:265
#, no-c-format
msgid "DNS Server Installation: DNS Zones"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: net_dns.xml:277
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"In the final dialog, you can open the DNS port in the firewall by clicking "
"<guimenu>Open Port in Firewall</guimenu> . Then decide whether to start the "
"DNS server when booting ( <guimenu>On</guimenu> or <guimenu>Off</guimenu> ). "
"You can also activate LDAP support. See <xref linkend=\"fig.yast2.dnsinst."
"finish\"/> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: net_dns.xml:285
#, no-c-format
msgid "DNS Server Installation: Finish Wizard"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: net_dns.xml:300
#, no-c-format
msgid "Expert Configuration"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: net_dns.xml:301
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"After starting the module, &yast; opens a window displaying several "
"configuration options. Completing it results in a DNS server configuration "
"with the basic functions in place:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: net_dns.xml:307
#, no-c-format
msgid "Start-Up"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: net_dns.xml:308
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Under <guimenu>Start-Up</guimenu> , define whether the DNS server should be "
"started when the booting the system or manually. To start the DNS server "
"immediately, click <guimenu>Start DNS Server Now</guimenu> . To stop the DNS "
"server, click <guimenu>Stop DNS Server Now</guimenu> . To save the current "
"settings, select <guimenu>Save Settings and Reload DNS Server Now</"
"guimenu> . <!-- <figure id=\"fig.yast2.dns.startup\"> <title>DNS Server: "
"Start-up</title> <screenshot> <mediaobject> <imageobject role=\"fo\"> "
"<imagedata width=\"75%\" fileref=\"yast2_dns_def_startup.png\" format=\"PNG"
"\"/> </imageobject> <imageobject role=\"html\"> <imagedata width=\"75%\" "
"fileref=\"yast2_dns_def_startup.png\" format=\"PNG\"/> </imageobject> </"
"mediaobject> </screenshot> </figure>--> You can open the DNS port in the "
"firewall with <guimenu>Open Port in Firewall</guimenu> and modify the "
"firewall settings with <guimenu>Firewall Details</guimenu> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: net_dns.xml:334
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"By selecting <guimenu>LDAP Support Active</guimenu> , the zone files are "
"managed by an LDAP database. Any changes to zone data written to the LDAP "
"database are picked up by the DNS server when it is restarted or prompted to "
"reload its configuration."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: net_dns.xml:342
#, no-c-format
msgid "Forwarders"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: net_dns.xml:343
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If your local DNS server cannot answer a request, it tries to forward the "
"request to a <guimenu>Forwarder</guimenu> , if configured so. This forwarder "
"may be added manually to the <guimenu>Forwarder List</guimenu> . If the "
"forwarder is not static like in dial-up connections, <guimenu>netconfig</"
"guimenu> handles the configuration. For more information about netconfig, "
"see <command>man 8 netconfig</command> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: net_dns.xml:353
#, no-c-format
msgid "Basic Options"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: net_dns.xml:354
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"In this section, set basic server options. From the <guimenu>Option</"
"guimenu> menu, select the desired item then specify the value in the "
"corresponding text box. Include the new entry by selecting <guimenu>Add</"
"guimenu> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: net_dns.xml:378
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"To set what the DNS server should log and how, select <guimenu>Logging</"
"guimenu> . Under <guimenu>Log Type</guimenu> , specify where the DNS server "
"should write the log data. Use the system-wide log by selecting "
"<guimenu>System Log</guimenu> or specify a different file by selecting "
"<guimenu>File</guimenu> . In the latter case, additionally specify a name, "
"the maximum file size in megabytes and the number of log file versions to "
"store."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: net_dns.xml:387
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Further options are available under <guimenu>Additional Logging</guimenu> . "
"Enabling <guimenu>Log All DNS Queries</guimenu> causes <emphasis>every</"
"emphasis> query to be logged, in which case the log file could grow "
"extremely large. For this reason, it is not a good idea to enable this "
"option for other than debugging purposes. To log the data traffic during "
"zone updates between DHCP and DNS server, enable <guimenu>Log Zone Updates</"
"guimenu> . To log the data traffic during a zone transfer from master to "
"slave, enable <guimenu>Log Zone Transfer</guimenu> . See <xref linkend=\"fig."
"yast2.dns.logging\"/> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: net_dns.xml:399
#, no-c-format
msgid "DNS Server: Logging"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: net_dns.xml:411
#, no-c-format
msgid "ACLs"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: net_dns.xml:412
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Use this dialog to define ACLs (access control lists) to enforce access "
"restrictions. After providing a distinct name under <guimenu>Name</"
"guimenu> , specify an IP address (with or without netmask) under "
"<guimenu>Value</guimenu> in the following fashion:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: net_dns.xml:418
#, no-c-format
msgid "{ 192.168.1/24; }"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: net_dns.xml:419
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The syntax of the configuration file requires that the address ends with a "
"semicolon and is put into curly braces."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: net_dns.xml:440
#, no-c-format
msgid "TSIG Keys"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: net_dns.xml:441
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The main purpose of TSIGs (transaction signatures) is to secure "
"communications between DHCP and DNS servers. They are described in <xref "
"linkend=\"sec.dns.tsig\"/> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: net_dns.xml:446
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"To generate a TSIG key, enter a distinctive name in the field labeled "
"<guimenu>Key ID</guimenu> and specify the file where the key should be "
"stored ( <guimenu>Filename</guimenu> ). Confirm your choices with "
"<guimenu>Generate</guimenu> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: net_dns.xml:452
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"To use a previously created key, leave the <guimenu>Key ID</guimenu> field "
"blank and select the file where it is stored under <guimenu>Filename</"
"guimenu> . After that, confirm with <guimenu>Add</guimenu> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: net_dns.xml:475
#, no-c-format
msgid "DNS Zones (Adding a Slave Zone)"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: net_dns.xml:476
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"To add a slave zone, select <guimenu>DNS Zones</guimenu> , choose the zone "
"type <guimenu>Slave</guimenu> , write the name of the new zone, and click "
"<guimenu>Add</guimenu> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: net_dns.xml:481
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"In the <guimenu>Zone Editor</guimenu> sub-dialog under <guimenu>Master DNS "
"Server IP</guimenu> , specify the master from which the slave should pull "
"its data. To limit access to the server, select one of the ACLs from the "
"list. <!-- See <xref linkend=\"fig.yast2.dns.zoneeditor\"/>. -->"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: net_dns.xml:502
#, no-c-format
msgid "DNS Zones (Adding a Master Zone)"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: net_dns.xml:503
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"To add a master zone, select <guimenu>DNS Zones</guimenu> , choose the zone "
"type <guimenu>Master</guimenu> , write the name of the new zone, and click "
"<guimenu>Add</guimenu> . When adding a master zone, a reverse zone is also "
"needed. For example, when adding the zone <systemitem>example.com</"
"systemitem> that points to hosts in a subnet <literal>192.168.1.0/24</"
"literal> , you should also add a reverse zone for the IP-address range "
"covered. By definition, this should be named <literal>1.168.192.in-addr."
"arpa</literal> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: net_dns.xml:515
#, no-c-format
msgid "DNS Zones (Editing a Master Zone)"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: net_dns.xml:516
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"To edit a master zone, select <guimenu>DNS Zones</guimenu> , select the "
"master zone from the table, and click <guimenu>Edit</guimenu> . The dialog "
"consists of several pages: <guimenu>Basics</guimenu> (the one opened first), "
"<guimenu>NS Records</guimenu> , <guimenu>MX Records</guimenu> , "
"<guimenu>SOA</guimenu> , and <guimenu>Records</guimenu> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: net_dns.xml:523
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The basic dialog, shown in <xref linkend=\"fig.yast2.dns.ddns\"/> , lets you "
"define settings for dynamic DNS and access options for zone transfers to "
"clients and slave name servers. To permit the dynamic updating of zones, "
"select <guimenu>Allow Dynamic Updates</guimenu> and the corresponding TSIG "
"key. The key must have been defined before the update action starts. To "
"enable zone transfers, select the corresponding ACLs. ACLs must have been "
"defined already."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: net_dns.xml:532
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"In the <guimenu>Basics</guimenu> dialog, select whether to enable zone "
"transfers. Use the listed ACLs to define who can download zones."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: net_dns.xml:537
#, no-c-format
msgid "DNS Server: Zone Editor (Basics)"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: net_dns.xml:549
#, no-c-format
msgid "Zone Editor (NS Records)"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: net_dns.xml:551
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The <guimenu>NS Records</guimenu> dialog allows you to define alternative "
"name servers for the zones specified. Make sure that your own name server is "
"included in the list. To add a record, enter its name under <guimenu>Name "
"Server to Add</guimenu> then confirm with <guimenu>Add</guimenu> . See <xref "
"linkend=\"fig.yast2.dns.nsrec\"/> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: net_dns.xml:559
#, no-c-format
msgid "DNS Server: Zone Editor (NS Records)"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: net_dns.xml:572
#, no-c-format
msgid "Zone Editor (MX Records)"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: net_dns.xml:574
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"To add a mail server for the current zone to the existing list, enter the "
"corresponding address and priority value. After doing so, confirm by "
"selecting <guimenu>Add</guimenu> . See <xref linkend=\"fig.yast2.dns.mxrec\"/"
"> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: net_dns.xml:581
#, no-c-format
msgid "DNS Server: Zone Editor (MX Records)"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: net_dns.xml:594
#, no-c-format
msgid "Zone Editor (SOA)"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: net_dns.xml:596
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"This page allows you to create SOA (start of authority) records. For an "
"explanation of the individual options, refer to <xref linkend=\"ex.welt.zone"
"\"/> . <phrase os=\"sles;osuse\">Changing SOA records is not supported for "
"dynamic zones managed via LDAP.</phrase>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: net_dns.xml:603
#, no-c-format
msgid "DNS Server: Zone Editor (SOA)"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: net_dns.xml:616
#, no-c-format
msgid "Zone Editor (Records)"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: net_dns.xml:618
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"This dialog manages name resolution. In <guimenu>Record Key</guimenu> , "
"enter the host name then select its type. The <guimenu>A</guimenu> type "
"represents the main entry. The value for this should be an IP address "
"(IPv4). Use <guimenu>AAAA</guimenu> for IPv6 addresses. <guimenu>CNAME</"
"guimenu> is an alias. Use the types <guimenu>NS</guimenu> and <guimenu>MX</"
"guimenu> for detailed or partial records that expand on the information "
"provided in the <guimenu>NS Records</guimenu> and <guimenu>MX Records</"
"guimenu> tabs. These three types resolve to an existing <literal>A</literal> "
"record. <guimenu>PTR</guimenu> is for reverse zones. It is the opposite of "
"an <literal>A</literal> record, for example:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: net_dns.xml:631
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"hostname.example.com. IN A 192.168.0.1\n"
"1.0.168.192.in-addr.arpa IN PTR hostname.example.com."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: net_dns.xml:637
#, no-c-format
msgid "Adding Reverse Zones"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: net_dns.xml:638
#, no-c-format
msgid "To add a reverse zone, follow this procedure:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: net_dns.xml:643
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Start <menuchoice><guimenu>&yast;</guimenu><guimenu>DNS Server</"
"guimenu><guimenu>DNS Zones</guimenu></menuchoice> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: net_dns.xml:649
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If you have not added a master forward zone, add it and <guimenu>Edit</"
"guimenu> it."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: net_dns.xml:655
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"In the <guimenu>Records</guimenu> tab, fill the corresponding "
"<guimenu>Record Key</guimenu> and <guimenu>Value</guimenu> , then add the "
"record with <guimenu>Add</guimenu> and confirm with <guimenu>OK</guimenu> . "
"If &yast; complains about a non-existing record for a name server, add it in "
"the <guimenu>NS Records</guimenu> tab."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: net_dns.xml:663
#, no-c-format
msgid "Adding a Record for a Master Zone"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: net_dns.xml:675
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Back in the <guimenu>DNS Zones</guimenu> window, add a reverse master zone."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: net_dns.xml:680
#, no-c-format
msgid "Adding a Reverse Zone"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: net_dns.xml:692
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<guimenu>Edit</guimenu> the reverse zone, and in the <guimenu>Records</"
"guimenu> tab, you can see the <guimenu>PTR: Reverse translation</guimenu> "
"record type. Add the corresponding <guimenu>Record Key</guimenu> and "
"<guimenu>Value</guimenu> , then click <guimenu>Add</guimenu> and confirm "
"with <guimenu>OK</guimenu> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: net_dns.xml:700
#, no-c-format
msgid "Adding a Reverse Record"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: net_dns.xml:710
#, no-c-format
msgid "Add a name server record if needed."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: net_dns.xml:716
#, no-c-format
msgid "Editing the Reverse Zone"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: net_dns.xml:717
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"After adding a forward zone, go back to the main menu and select the reverse "
"zone for editing. There in the tab <guimenu>Basics</guimenu> activate the "
"check box <guimenu>Automatically Generate Records From</guimenu> and select "
"your forward zone. That way, all changes to the forward zone are "
"automatically updated in the reverse zone."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: net_dns.xml:730
#, no-c-format
msgid "Starting the BIND Name Server"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: net_dns.xml:732
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"On a &productnamereg; system, the name server BIND ( <emphasis>Berkeley "
"Internet Name Domain</emphasis> ) comes preconfigured, so it can be started "
"right after installation without any problems. Normally, if you already have "
"an Internet connection and entered <systemitem class=\"ipaddress"
"\">127.0.0.1</systemitem> as the name server address for <systemitem class="
"\"domainname\">localhost</systemitem> in <filename>/etc/resolv.conf</"
"filename> , you already have a working name resolution without needing to "
"know the DNS of the provider. BIND carries out name resolution via the root "
"name server, a notably slower process. Normally, the DNS of the provider "
"should be entered with its IP address in the configuration file <filename>/"
"etc/named.conf</filename> under <systemitem>forwarders</systemitem> to "
"ensure effective and secure name resolution. If this works so far, the name "
"server runs as a pure <emphasis>caching-only</emphasis> name server. Only "
"when you configure its own zones it becomes a proper DNS. Find a simple "
"example documented in <filename>/usr/share/doc/packages/bind/config</"
"filename> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: net_dns.xml:751
#, no-c-format
msgid "Automatic Adaptation of the Name Server Information"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: net_dns.xml:752
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Depending on the type of Internet connection or the network connection, the "
"name server information can automatically be adapted to the current "
"conditions. To do this, set the <systemitem>NETCONFIG_DNS_POLICY</"
"systemitem> variable in the <filename>/etc/sysconfig/network/config</"
"filename> file to <literal>auto</literal> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: net_dns.xml:762
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"However, do not set up an official domain until one is assigned to you by "
"the responsible institution. Even if you have your own domain and it is "
"managed by the provider, you are better off not using it, because BIND would "
"otherwise not forward requests for this domain. The Web server at the "
"provider, for example, would not be accessible for this domain."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: net_dns.xml:770
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"To start the name server, enter the command <command>systemctl start named</"
"command> as <systemitem class=\"username\">root</systemitem> . Check with "
"<command>systemctl status named</command> whether named (as the name server "
"process is called) has been started successfully. Test the name server "
"immediately on the local system with the <command>host</command> or "
"<command>dig</command> programs, which should return <systemitem class="
"\"domainname\">localhost</systemitem> as the default server with the address "
"<systemitem class=\"ipaddress\">127.0.0.1</systemitem> . If this is not the "
"case, <filename>/etc/resolv.conf</filename> probably contains an incorrect "
"name server entry or the file does not exist. For the first test, enter "
"<command>host</command> &nbsp; <option>127.0.0.1</option> , which should "
"always work. If you get an error message, use <command>systemctl status "
"named</command> to see whether the server is actually running. If the name "
"server does not start or behaves unexpectedly, check the output of "
"<command>journalctl -e</command> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: net_dns.xml:790
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"To use the name server of the provider (or one already running on your "
"network) as the forwarder, enter the corresponding IP address or addresses "
"in the <systemitem>options</systemitem> section under "
"<systemitem>forwarders</systemitem> . The addresses included in <xref "
"linkend=\"ex.forward\"/> are examples only. Adjust these entries to your own "
"setup."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: net_dns.xml:800
#, no-c-format
msgid "Forwarding Options in named.conf"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: net_dns.xml:804
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"options {\n"
"        directory \"/var/lib/named\";\n"
"        forwarders { 10.11.12.13; 10.11.12.14; };\n"
"        listen-on { 127.0.0.1; &dnsip;; };\n"
"        allow-query { 127/8; 192.168/16 };\n"
"        notify no;\n"
"};"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: net_dns.xml:813
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The <systemitem>options</systemitem> entry is followed by entries for the "
"zone, <systemitem class=\"domainname\">localhost</systemitem> , and "
"<systemitem>0.0.127.in-addr.arpa</systemitem> . The <literal>type hint</"
"literal> entry under <quote>.</quote> should always be present. The "
"corresponding files do not need to be modified and should work as they are. "
"Also make sure that each entry is closed with a <quote>;</quote> and that "
"the curly braces are in the correct places. After changing the configuration "
"file <filename>/etc/named.conf</filename> or the zone files, tell BIND to "
"reread them with <command>systemctl reload named</command> . Achieve the "
"same by stopping and restarting the name server with <command>systemctl "
"restart named</command> . Stop the server at any time by entering "
"<command>systemctl stop named</command> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: net_dns.xml:829
#, no-c-format
msgid "The /etc/named.conf Configuration File"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: net_dns.xml:831
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"All the settings for the BIND name server itself are stored in the "
"<filename>/etc/named.conf</filename> file. However, the zone data for the "
"domains to handle (consisting of the host names, IP addresses, and so on) "
"are stored in separate files in the <filename>/var/lib/named</filename> "
"directory. The details of this are described later."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: net_dns.xml:839
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<filename>/etc/named.conf</filename> is roughly divided into two areas. One "
"is the <systemitem>options</systemitem> section for general settings and the "
"other consists of <systemitem>zone</systemitem> entries for the individual "
"domains. A <systemitem>logging</systemitem> section and <systemitem>acl</"
"systemitem> (access control list) entries are optional. Comment lines begin "
"with a <literal>#</literal> sign or <literal>//</literal> . A minimal "
"<filename>/etc/named.conf</filename> is shown in <xref linkend=\"ex.named."
"mini\"/> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: net_dns.xml:851
#, no-c-format
msgid "A Basic /etc/named.conf"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: net_dns.xml:852
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"options {\n"
"        directory \"/var/lib/named\";\n"
"        forwarders { 10.0.0.1; };\n"
"        notify no;\n"
"};\n"
"\n"
"zone \"localhost\" in {\n"
"       type master;\n"
"       file \"localhost.zone\";\n"
"};\n"
"\n"
"zone \"0.0.127.in-addr.arpa\" in {\n"
"        type master;\n"
"        file \"127.0.0.zone\";\n"
"};\n"
"\n"
"zone \".\" in {\n"
"        type hint;\n"
"        file \"root.hint\";\n"
"};"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: net_dns.xml:875
#, no-c-format
msgid "Important Configuration Options"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: net_dns.xml:878
#, no-c-format
msgid "directory \" <replaceable>FILENAME</replaceable> \";"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: net_dns.xml:880
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Specifies the directory in which BIND can find the files containing the zone "
"data. Usually, this is <filename>/var/lib/named</filename> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: net_dns.xml:887
#, no-c-format
msgid "forwarders { <replaceable>IP-ADDRESS</replaceable> ; };"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: net_dns.xml:889
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Specifies the name servers (mostly of the provider) to which DNS requests "
"should be forwarded if they cannot be resolved directly. Replace "
"<replaceable>IP-ADDRESS</replaceable> with an IP address like "
"<literal>&dnsip;</literal> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: net_dns.xml:898
#, no-c-format
msgid "forward first;"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: net_dns.xml:900
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Causes DNS requests to be forwarded before an attempt is made to resolve "
"them via the root name servers. Instead of <systemitem>forward first</"
"systemitem> , <systemitem>forward only</systemitem> can be written to have "
"all requests forwarded and none sent to the root name servers. This makes "
"sense for firewall configurations."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: net_dns.xml:910
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"listen-on port 53 { 127.0.0.1; <replaceable>IP-ADDRESS</replaceable> ; };"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: net_dns.xml:912
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Tells BIND on which network interfaces and port to accept client queries. "
"<literal>port 53</literal> does not need to be specified explicitly, because "
"<literal>53</literal> is the default port. Enter <literal>127.0.0.1</"
"literal> to permit requests from the local host. If you omit this entry "
"entirely, all interfaces are used by default."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: net_dns.xml:922
#, no-c-format
msgid "listen-on-v6 port 53 {any; };"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: net_dns.xml:924
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Tells BIND on which port it should listen for IPv6 client requests. The only "
"alternative to <literal>any</literal> is <literal>none</literal> . As far as "
"IPv6 is concerned, the server only accepts wild card addresses."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: net_dns.xml:933
#, no-c-format
msgid "query-source address * port 53;"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: net_dns.xml:935
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"This entry is necessary if a firewall is blocking outgoing DNS requests. "
"This tells BIND to post requests externally from port 53 and not from any of "
"the high ports above 1024."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: net_dns.xml:943
#, no-c-format
msgid "query-source-v6 address * port 53;"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: net_dns.xml:945
#, no-c-format
msgid "Tells BIND which port to use for IPv6 queries."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: net_dns.xml:951
#, no-c-format
msgid "allow-query { 127.0.0.1; <replaceable>NET</replaceable> ; };"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: net_dns.xml:953
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Defines the networks from which clients can post DNS requests. Replace "
"<replaceable>NET</replaceable> with address information like "
"<literal>&subnetIImask;</literal> . The <systemitem>/24</systemitem> at the "
"end is an abbreviated expression for the netmask (in this case <systemitem "
"class=\"netmask\">255.255.255.0</systemitem> )."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: net_dns.xml:963
#, no-c-format
msgid "allow-transfer ! *;;"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: net_dns.xml:965
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Controls which hosts can request zone transfers. In the example, such "
"requests are completely denied with <systemitem>! *</systemitem> . Without "
"this entry, zone transfers can be requested from anywhere without "
"restrictions."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: net_dns.xml:974
#, no-c-format
msgid "statistics-interval 0;"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: net_dns.xml:976
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"In the absence of this entry, BIND generates several lines of statistical "
"information per hour in the system's journal. Set it to 0 to suppress these "
"statistics completely or set an interval in minutes."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: net_dns.xml:984
#, no-c-format
msgid "cleaning-interval 720;"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: net_dns.xml:986
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"This option defines at which time intervals BIND clears its cache. This "
"triggers an entry in the system's journal each time it occurs. The time "
"specification is in minutes. The default is 60 minutes."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: net_dns.xml:994
#, no-c-format
msgid "interface-interval 0;"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: net_dns.xml:996
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"BIND regularly searches the network interfaces for new or nonexistent "
"interfaces. If this value is set to <systemitem>0</systemitem> , this is not "
"done and BIND only listens at the interfaces detected at start-up. "
"Otherwise, the interval can be defined in minutes. The default is sixty "
"minutes."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: net_dns.xml:1006
#, no-c-format
msgid "notify no;"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: net_dns.xml:1008
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<option>no</option> prevents other name servers from being informed when "
"changes are made to the zone data or when the name server is restarted."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: net_dns.xml:1015
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"For a list of available options, read the manual page <command>man 5 named."
"conf</command> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: net_dns.xml:1022
#, no-c-format
msgid "Logging"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: net_dns.xml:1023
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"What, how, and where logging takes place can be extensively configured in "
"BIND. Normally, the default settings should be sufficient. <xref linkend="
"\"ex.no.log\"/> , shows the simplest form of such an entry and completely "
"suppresses any logging."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: net_dns.xml:1030
#, no-c-format
msgid "Entry to Disable Logging"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: net_dns.xml:1031
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"logging {\n"
"        category default { null; };\n"
"};"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: net_dns.xml:1038
#, no-c-format
msgid "Zone Entries"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: net_dns.xml:1040
#, no-c-format
msgid "Zone Entry for example.com"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: net_dns.xml:1041
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"zone \"example.com\" in {\n"
"      type master;\n"
"      file \"example.com.zone\";\n"
"      notify no;\n"
"};"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: net_dns.xml:1047
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"After <systemitem>zone</systemitem> , specify the name of the domain to "
"administer ( <systemitem class=\"domainname\">example.com</systemitem> ) "
"followed by <systemitem>in</systemitem> and a block of relevant options "
"enclosed in curly braces, as shown in <xref linkend=\"ex.meine.domain\"/> . "
"To define a <emphasis>slave zone</emphasis> , switch the <systemitem>type</"
"systemitem> to <literal>slave</literal> and specify a name server that "
"administers this zone as <literal>master</literal> (which, in turn, may be a "
"slave of another master), as shown in <xref linkend=\"ex.andere.domain\"/> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: net_dns.xml:1059
#, no-c-format
msgid "Zone Entry for &exampledomain1;"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: net_dns.xml:1060
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"zone \"&exampledomain1;\" in {\n"
"      type slave;\n"
"      file \"slave/&exampledomain1;.zone\";\n"
"      masters { 10.0.0.1; }; <!-- network scheme: What is this external DNS' "
"IP supposed to be?\n"
"      bg: we still did not define the addresses of a public internet.-->\n"
"};"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: net_dns.xml:1067
#, no-c-format
msgid "The zone options:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: net_dns.xml:1072
#, no-c-format
msgid "type master;"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: net_dns.xml:1074
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"By specifying <literal>master</literal> , tell BIND that the zone is handled "
"by the local name server. This assumes that a zone file has been created in "
"the correct format."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: net_dns.xml:1082
#, no-c-format
msgid "type slave;"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: net_dns.xml:1084
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"This zone is transferred from another name server. It must be used together "
"with <systemitem>masters</systemitem> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: net_dns.xml:1091
#, no-c-format
msgid "type hint;"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: net_dns.xml:1093
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The zone <literal>.</literal> of the <literal>hint</literal> type is used to "
"set the root name servers. This zone definition can be left as is."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: net_dns.xml:1101
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"file <filename>&exampledomain;.zone</filename> or file <quote>slave/"
"&exampledomain1;.zone</quote> ;"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: net_dns.xml:1104
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"This entry specifies the file where zone data for the domain is located. "
"This file is not required for a slave, because this data is pulled from "
"another name server. To differentiate master and slave files, use the "
"directory <filename>slave</filename> for the slave files."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: net_dns.xml:1113
#, no-c-format
msgid "masters { <replaceable>SERVER_IP_ADDRESS</replaceable> ; };"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: net_dns.xml:1115
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"This entry is only needed for slave zones. It specifies from which name "
"server the zone file should be transferred."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: net_dns.xml:1122
#, no-c-format
msgid "allow-update {! *; };"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: net_dns.xml:1124
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"This option controls external write access, which would allow clients to "
"make a DNS entry&mdash;something not normally desirable for security "
"reasons. Without this entry, zone updates are not allowed. The above entry "
"achieves the same because <literal>! *</literal> effectively bans any such "
"activity."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: net_dns.xml:1137
#, no-c-format
msgid "Zone Files"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: net_dns.xml:1139
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Two types of zone files are needed. One assigns IP addresses to host names "
"and the other does the reverse: it supplies a host name for an IP address."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: net_dns.xml:1145
#, no-c-format
msgid "Using the Dot (Period, Fullstop) in Zone Files"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: net_dns.xml:1146
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The <literal>\".\"</literal> has an important meaning in the zone files. If "
"host names are given without a final dot ( <literal>.</literal> ), the zone "
"is appended. Complete host names specified with a full domain name must end "
"with a dot ( <literal>.</literal> ) to avoid having the domain added to it "
"again. A missing or wrongly placed \".\" is probably the most frequent cause "
"of name server configuration errors."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: net_dns.xml:1189
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The first case to consider is the zone file <filename>&exampledomain;.zone</"
"filename> , responsible for the domain <filename>&exampledomain;</"
"filename> , shown in <xref linkend=\"ex.welt.zone\"/> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: net_dns.xml:1199
#, no-c-format
msgid "The /var/lib/named/&exampledomain;.zone File"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: net_dns.xml:1200
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"1.  $TTL 2D\n"
"2.  &exampledomain;. IN SOA      dns  root.&exampledomain;. ( <!-- network "
"scheme: need short hostname -->\n"
"3.               2003072441  ; serial\n"
"4.               1D          ; refresh\n"
"5.               2H          ; retry\n"
"6.               1W          ; expiry\n"
"7.               2D )        ; minimum\n"
"8.\n"
"9.               IN NS       dns <!-- network scheme: need short hostname --"
">\n"
"10.              IN MX       10 mail\n"
"11.\n"
"12. gate         IN A        &gateip; <!-- network scheme: need short "
"hostname -->\n"
"13.              IN A        10.0.0.1 <!-- network scheme: What's the "
"external IP of the gate in the WAN? -->\n"
"14. dns          IN A        &dnsip; <!-- network scheme: need short "
"hostname -->\n"
"15. mail         IN A        &mailip; <!-- network scheme: need short "
"hostname -->\n"
"16. &wsI;      IN A        &wsIip;\n"
"17. &wsII;        IN A        &wsIIip;\n"
"18. &wsIII;       IN A        &wsIIIip;\n"
"19. &wsIV;      IN A        &wsIVip;\n"
"20. ntp          IN CNAME    dns <!-- network scheme: need short hostname --"
">\n"
"21. dns6         IN A6  0    &dnsipv6;\n"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: net_dns.xml:1236
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<systemitem>$TTL</systemitem> defines the default time to live that should "
"apply to all the entries in this file. In this example, entries are valid "
"for a period of two days ( <literal>2 D</literal> )."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: net_dns.xml:1246
#, no-c-format
msgid "This is where the SOA (start of authority) control record begins:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: net_dns.xml:1251
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The name of the domain to administer is <literal>&exampledomain;</literal> "
"in the first position. This ends with <literal>\".\"</literal> , because "
"otherwise the zone would be appended a second time. Alternatively, "
"<literal>@</literal> can be entered here, in which case the zone would be "
"extracted from the corresponding entry in <filename>/etc/named.conf</"
"filename> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: net_dns.xml:1261
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"After <systemitem>IN SOA</systemitem> is the name of the name server in "
"charge as master for this zone. The name is expanded from <literal>dns</"
"literal> to <literal>&dnsname;</literal> , because it does not end with a "
"<literal>\".\"</literal> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: net_dns.xml:1269
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"An e-mail address of the person in charge of this name server follows. "
"Because the <literal>@</literal> sign already has a special meaning, "
"<literal>\".\"</literal> is entered here instead. For "
"<systemitem>root@&exampledomain;</systemitem> the entry must read "
"<systemitem>root.&exampledomain;.</systemitem> . The <literal>\".\"</"
"literal> must be included at the end to prevent the zone from being added."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: net_dns.xml:1280
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The <literal>(</literal> includes all lines up to <literal>)</literal> into "
"the SOA record."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: net_dns.xml:1289
#, no-c-format
msgid "Line 3:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: net_dns.xml:1291
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The <systemitem>serial number</systemitem> is an arbitrary number that is "
"increased each time this file is changed. It is needed to inform the "
"secondary name servers (slave servers) of changes. For this, a 10 digit "
"number of the date and run number, written as YYYYMMDDNN, has become the "
"customary format."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: net_dns.xml:1312
#, no-c-format
msgid "Line 4:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: net_dns.xml:1314
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The <systemitem>refresh rate</systemitem> specifies the time interval at "
"which the secondary name servers verify the zone <systemitem>serial number</"
"systemitem> . In this case, one day."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: net_dns.xml:1322
#, no-c-format
msgid "Line 5:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: net_dns.xml:1324
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The <systemitem>retry rate</systemitem> specifies the time interval at which "
"a secondary name server, in case of error, attempts to contact the primary "
"server again. Here, two hours."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: net_dns.xml:1332
#, no-c-format
msgid "Line 6:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: net_dns.xml:1334
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The <systemitem>expiration time</systemitem> specifies the time frame after "
"which a secondary name server discards the cached data if it has not "
"regained contact to the primary server. Here, a week."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: net_dns.xml:1342
#, no-c-format
msgid "Line 7:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: net_dns.xml:1344
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The last entry in the SOA record specifies the <systemitem>negative caching "
"TTL</systemitem> &mdash;the time for which results of unresolved DNS queries "
"from other servers may be cached."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: net_dns.xml:1354
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The <systemitem>IN NS</systemitem> specifies the name server responsible for "
"this domain. <systemitem>dns</systemitem> is extended to "
"<systemitem>&dnsname;</systemitem> because it does not end with a <literal>"
"\".\"</literal> . There can be several lines like this&mdash;one for the "
"primary and one for each secondary name server. If <systemitem>notify</"
"systemitem> is not set to <option>no</option> in <filename>/etc/named.conf</"
"filename> , all the name servers listed here are informed of the changes "
"made to the zone data."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: net_dns.xml:1367
#, no-c-format
msgid "Line 10:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: net_dns.xml:1369
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The MX record specifies the mail server that accepts, processes, and "
"forwards e-mails for the domain <systemitem class=\"domainname"
"\">&exampledomain;</systemitem> . In this example, this is the host "
"<systemitem class=\"domainname\">&mailname;</systemitem> . The number in "
"front of the host name is the preference value. If there are multiple MX "
"entries, the mail server with the smallest value is taken first. If mail "
"delivery to this server fails, the entry with the next-smallest value is "
"used."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: net_dns.xml:1382
#, no-c-format
msgid "Lines 12&ndash;19:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: net_dns.xml:1384
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"These are the actual address records where one or more IP addresses are "
"assigned to host names. The names are listed here without a <literal>\".\"</"
"literal> because they do not include their domain, so <systemitem class="
"\"domainname\">&exampledomain;</systemitem> is added to all of them. Two IP "
"addresses are assigned to the host <systemitem>gate</systemitem> , as it has "
"two network cards. <!-- network scheme: need short hostname --> <!-- looks "
"as if we don't support A6 at least with YAST --> Wherever the host address "
"is a traditional one (IPv4), the record is marked with <literal>A</"
"literal> . If the address is an IPv6 address, the entry is marked with "
"<literal>AAAA</literal> . <!-- The previous token for IPv6 addresses was "
"only <literal>AAAA</literal>, which is now obsolete. -->"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: net_dns.xml:1403
#, no-c-format
msgid "IPv6 Syntax"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: net_dns.xml:1404
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The IPv6 record has a slightly different syntax than IPv4. Because of the "
"fragmentation possibility, it is necessary to provide information about "
"missed bits before the address. To fill up the IPv6 address with the needed "
"number of <quote>0</quote> , add two colons at the correct place in the "
"address. <!-- You must provide this information even if you want to use a "
"completely unfragmented address. For the AAAA record with the syntax -->"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: net_dns.xml:1414
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"pluto     AAAA 2345:00C1:CA11::1234:5678:9ABC:DEF0\n"
"pluto     AAAA 2345:00D2:DA11::1234:5678:9ABC:DEF0"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: net_dns.xml:1427
#, no-c-format
msgid "Line 20:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: net_dns.xml:1429
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The alias <literal>ntp</literal> can be used to address <!-- network scheme: "
"need short hostname --> <literal>dns</literal> ( <systemitem>CNAME</"
"systemitem> means <!-- network scheme: need short hostname --> "
"<emphasis>canonical name</emphasis> )."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: net_dns.xml:1442
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The pseudo domain <literal>in-addr.arpa</literal> is used for the reverse "
"lookup of IP addresses into host names. It is appended to the network part "
"of the address in reverse notation. So <systemitem class=\"ipaddress"
"\">192.168</systemitem> is resolved into <systemitem>168.192.in-addr.arpa</"
"systemitem> . See <xref linkend=\"dat.arpa\"/> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: net_dns.xml:1454
#, no-c-format
msgid "Reverse Lookup"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: net_dns.xml:1455
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"1.  $TTL 2D\n"
"2.  168.192.in-addr.arpa.   IN SOA &dnsname;. root.&exampledomain;. (\n"
"3.                          2003072441      ; serial\n"
"4.                          1D              ; refresh\n"
"5.                          2H              ; retry\n"
"6.                          1W              ; expiry\n"
"7.                          2D )            ; minimum\n"
"8.\n"
"9.                          IN NS           &dnsname;.\n"
"10.\n"
"11. 1.5                     IN PTR          &gatename;. <!-- network scheme: "
"need IP suffix for this -->\n"
"12. 100.3                   IN PTR          &wwwname;. <!-- network scheme: "
"need IP suffix for this -->\n"
"13. 253.2                   IN PTR          &cupsname;. <!-- network scheme: "
"need IP suffix for this -->"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: net_dns.xml:1472
#, no-c-format
msgid "Line 1:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: net_dns.xml:1474
#, no-c-format
msgid "$TTL defines the standard TTL that applies to all entries here."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: net_dns.xml:1480
#, no-c-format
msgid "Line 2:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: net_dns.xml:1482
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<!--adjust to standard network example--> The configuration file should "
"activate reverse lookup for the network <systemitem class=\"ipaddress"
"\">192.168</systemitem> . Given <!-- network scheme: Two-octet prefix "
"needed. --> that the zone is called <systemitem>168.192.in-addr.arpa</"
"systemitem> , it should not be added to the host names. Therefore, all host "
"names are entered in their complete form&mdash;with their domain and with a "
"<literal>\".\"</literal> at the end. The remaining entries correspond to "
"those described for the previous <systemitem>&exampledomain;</systemitem> "
"example."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: net_dns.xml:1497
#, no-c-format
msgid "Lines 3&ndash;7:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: net_dns.xml:1499
#, no-c-format
msgid "See the previous example for <systemitem>&exampledomain;</systemitem> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: net_dns.xml:1505
#, no-c-format
msgid "Line 9:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: net_dns.xml:1507
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Again this line specifies the name server responsible for this zone. This "
"time, however, the name is entered in its complete form with the domain and "
"a <literal>\".\"</literal> at the end."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: net_dns.xml:1515
#, no-c-format
msgid "Lines 11&ndash;13:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: net_dns.xml:1517
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"These are the pointer records hinting at the IP addresses on the respective "
"hosts. Only the last part of the IP address is entered at the beginning of "
"the line, without the <literal>\".\"</literal> at the end. Appending the "
"zone to this (without the <systemitem>.in-addr.arpa</systemitem> ) results "
"in the complete IP address in reverse order."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: net_dns.xml:1529
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Normally, zone transfers between different versions of BIND should be "
"possible without any problems."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: net_dns.xml:1536
#, no-c-format
msgid "Dynamic Update of Zone Data"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: net_dns.xml:1538
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The term <emphasis>dynamic update</emphasis> refers to operations by which "
"entries in the zone files of a master server are added, changed, or deleted. "
"This mechanism is described in RFC&nbsp;2136. Dynamic update is configured "
"individually for each zone entry by adding an optional <systemitem>allow-"
"update</systemitem> or <systemitem>update-policy</systemitem> rule. Zones to "
"update dynamically should not be edited by hand."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: net_dns.xml:1548
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Transmit the entries to update to the server with the command "
"<command>nsupdate</command> . For the exact syntax of this command, check "
"the manual page for nsupdate ( <command>man</command> &nbsp; <option>8 "
"nsupdate</option> ). For security reasons, any such update should be "
"performed using TSIG keys as described in <xref linkend=\"sec.dns.tsig\"/> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: net_dns.xml:1557
#, no-c-format
msgid "Secure Transactions"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: net_dns.xml:1559
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Secure transactions can be made with transaction signatures (TSIGs) based on "
"shared secret keys (also called TSIG keys). This section describes how to "
"generate and use such keys."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: net_dns.xml:1565
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Secure transactions are needed for communication between different servers "
"and for the dynamic update of zone data. Making the access control dependent "
"on keys is much more secure than merely relying on IP addresses."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: net_dns.xml:1571
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Generate a TSIG key with the following command (for details, see "
"<command>man</command> &nbsp; <option>dnssec-keygen</option> ):"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: net_dns.xml:1576
#, no-c-format
msgid "&prompt.sudo;dnssec-keygen -a hmac-md5 -b 128 -n HOST host1-host2"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: net_dns.xml:1578
#, no-c-format
msgid "This creates two files with names similar to these:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: net_dns.xml:1582
#, no-c-format
msgid "Khost1-host2.+157+34265.private Khost1-host2.+157+34265.key"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: net_dns.xml:1584
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The key itself (a string like <literal>ejIkuCyyGJwwuN3xAteKgg==</literal> ) "
"is found in both files. To use it for transactions, the second file "
"( <filename>Khost1-host2.+157+34265.key</filename> ) must be transferred to "
"the remote host, preferably in a secure way (using scp, for example). On the "
"remote server, the key must be included in the <filename>/etc/named.conf</"
"filename> file to enable a secure communication between <literal>host1</"
"literal> and <literal>host2</literal> :"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: net_dns.xml:1594
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"key host1-host2 {\n"
" algorithm hmac-md5;\n"
" secret \"ejIkuCyyGJwwuN3xAteKgg==\";\n"
"};"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: net_dns.xml:1600
#, no-c-format
msgid "File Permissions of <filename>/etc/named.conf</filename>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: net_dns.xml:1601
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Make sure that the permissions of <filename>/etc/named.conf</filename> are "
"properly restricted. The default for this file is <literal>0640</literal> , "
"with the owner being <systemitem class=\"username\">root</systemitem> and "
"the group <systemitem class=\"username\">named</systemitem> . As an "
"alternative, move the keys to an extra file with specially limited "
"permissions, which is then included from <filename>/etc/named.conf</"
"filename> . To include an external file, use:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: net_dns.xml:1610
#, no-c-format
msgid "include  \"filename\""
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: net_dns.xml:1611
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Replace <option>filename</option> with an absolute path to your file with "
"keys."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: net_dns.xml:1617
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<!--adjust to standard network example--> <!-- network schema: We have no "
"2xDNS setup, i used a disjoint network for --> <!-- this. Is this a problem? "
"After all, this is just an illustration of how --> <!-- to put a key for a "
"host, and not a beginner topic. Anyway, we'd need a --> <!-- secondary "
"server. --> To enable the server <literal>host1</literal> to use the key for "
"<literal>host2</literal> (which has the address <literal>10.1.2.3</literal> "
"in this example), the server's <filename>/etc/named.conf</filename> must "
"include the following rule:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: net_dns.xml:1629
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"server 10.1.2.3 {\n"
"  keys { host1-host2. ;};\n"
"};"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: net_dns.xml:1633
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Analogous entries must be included in the configuration files of "
"<literal>host2</literal> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: net_dns.xml:1638
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Add TSIG keys for any ACLs (access control lists, not to be confused with "
"file system ACLs) that are defined for IP addresses and address ranges to "
"enable transaction security. The corresponding entry could look like this:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: net_dns.xml:1644
#, no-c-format
msgid "allow-update { key host1-host2. ;};"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: net_dns.xml:1646
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"This topic is discussed in more detail in the <emphasis>BIND Administrator "
"Reference Manual</emphasis> under <literal>update-policy</literal> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: net_dns.xml:1652
#, no-c-format
msgid "DNS Security"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: net_dns.xml:1654
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"DNSSEC, or DNS security, is described in RFC&nbsp;2535. The tools available "
"for DNSSEC are discussed in the BIND Manual."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: net_dns.xml:1659
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"A zone considered secure must have one or several zone keys associated with "
"it. These are generated with <command>dnssec-keygen</command> , as are the "
"host keys. The DSA encryption algorithm is currently used to generate these "
"keys. The public keys generated should be included in the corresponding zone "
"file with an <systemitem>$INCLUDE</systemitem> rule."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: net_dns.xml:1667
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"With the command <command>dnssec-signzone</command> , you can create sets of "
"generated keys ( <literal>keyset-</literal> files), transfer them to the "
"parent zone in a secure manner, and sign them. This generates the files to "
"include for each zone in <filename>/etc/named.conf</filename> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: net_dns.xml:1687
#, no-c-format
msgid "For More Information"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: net_dns.xml:1689
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"For more information, see the <emphasis>BIND Administrator Reference Manual</"
"emphasis> from the <systemitem class=\"resource\">bind-doc</systemitem> "
"package, which is installed under <filename>/usr/share/doc/packages/bind/"
"arm</filename> . Consider additionally consulting the RFCs referenced by the "
"manual and the manual pages included with BIND. <filename>/usr/share/doc/"
"packages/bind/README.SUSE</filename> contains up-to-date information about "
"BIND in &productname;."
msgstr ""
